{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/5pzkgl","slide":4,"text":"Here is the product in one line: a source-labelled signal becomes a case, the system extracts and resolves what it can, scores corridor risk, and then stops. The analyst sees and confirms the assumptions. Only then do the simulation and portfolio comparison run. The outcome is recorded locally—never sent as a purchase order or supplier instruction.\n\nTransition: That workflow is deliberately structured so AI has a precise job, not unchecked authority."}
